The paper deals with unsupervised machine learning of natural language, which falls under the category of computational linguistics (cs.CL). The paper also discusses various statistical models and algorithms, which are commonly used in machine learning (cs.LG). Additionally, the paper examines the validity of the Argument from the Poverty of the Stimulus, which is a philosophical argument related to language acquisition, and thus could be categorized under artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also presents novel algorithms for learning various parts of natural languages, which could fall under neural networks (cs.NE) or software engineering (cs.SD) categories.
